about.summary: A fast reimplementation of several density-based algorithms of the DBSCAN family for spatial data. Includes the DBSCAN (density-based spatial clustering of applications with noise) and OPTICS (ordering points to identify the clustering structure) clustering algorithms HDBSCAN (hierarchical DBSCAN) and the LOF (local outlier factor) algorithm. The implementations use the kd-tree data structure (from library ANN) for faster k-nearest neighbor search. An R interface to fast kNN and fixed-radius NN search is also provided.

{% set version = "1.2.2" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-dbscan
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/dbscan_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/dbscan/dbscan_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0c3abdd122521d9be8cbdb3589a91a18ef18a3d00493fdb140fd932bae0fe343

build:
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ stdlib("c") }}                # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ stdlib("m2w64_c") }}          # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-rcpp >=1.0.0               # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-generics
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=1.0.0
    - r-generics
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=1.0.0
    - r-generics

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('dbscan')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('dbscan')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/mhahsler/dbscan
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: A fast reimplementation of several density-based algorithms of the DBSCAN family for spatial data. Includes the DBSCAN (density-based spatial clustering of applications with noise) and OPTICS (ordering points to identify the clustering structure) clustering algorithms HDBSCAN (hierarchical DBSCAN) and the LOF
    (local outlier factor) algorithm. The implementations use the kd-tree data structure (from library ANN) for faster k-nearest neighbor search. An R interface to fast kNN and fixed-radius NN search is also provided.
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
